# Meerkat — backup before every edit

Before **creating or changing** any project file (code, docs, Cursor rules), the agent **must** rotate a local backup **first**. Do not skip this for “small” edits.

## What to back up

| Path | Backup method |
|------|----------------|
| `meerk40t/**/*.py` and other source under `meerk40t/` | Rotate **`.bak.1` → `.bak.2` → `.bak.3`** (keep 3) |
| `docs/meerk40t/**` | Same `.bak.N` rotation beside the file |
| `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` | Same `.bak.N` rotation beside the file |

## PowerShell (run once per file, before editing)

```powershell
$p = 'C:\Users\User\Ai Projects\meerkat\path\to\file.py'
$b1 = "$p.bak.1"
$b2 = "$p.bak.2"
$b3 = "$p.bak.3"
if (Test-Path $b3) { Remove-Item $b3 -Force }
if (Test-Path $b2) { Move-Item $b2 $b3 -Force }
if (Test-Path $b1) { Move-Item $b1 $b2 -Force }
Copy-Item $p $b1 -Force
```

## Agent checklist

1. **Backup** target file(s).
2. **Edit** canonical file only.
3. **Update** `docs/meerk40t/` when behavior or workflows change (see `meerk40t-knowledge-base.mdc` §5).

